Package datastructures

Contains general purpose datastructures.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IdNoGenerator
    Interface for creatiing unique identification number.
    Observers<ObjectType>
    Interface to observe changes on objects for syncronisatiation purposes.
    PlanarDelaunayTriangulation.Storable
    Interface with funktionality required for objects to be used in a planar triangulation.
    ShapeTree.Storable
    Interface, which must be implemented by objects to be stored in a ShapeTree.
    Stoppable
    Interface for stoppable threads.
    UndoableObjects.Storable
    Conditiom for an Object to be stored in an UndoableObjects database.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ArrayStack<p_element_type>  
    BigIntAux
    Auxiliary functions with BigInteger Parameters
    FileFilter
    Used in the file chooser to filter all files which do not have an extension from the input array.
    IdentifierType
    Describes legal identifiers together with the character used for string quotes.
    IndentFileWriter
    Handles the indenting of scopes while writing to an output text file.
    MinAreaTree
    Binary search tree for shapes in the plane.
    PlanarDelaunayTriangulation
    Creates a Delaunay triangulation in the plane for the input objects.
    PlanarDelaunayTriangulation.ResultEdge
    Describes a line segment in the result of the Delaunay Triangulation.
    ShapeTree
    Abstract binary search tree for shapes in the plane.
    ShapeTree.InnerNode
    Desscription of an inner node of the tree, which implements a fork to its two children.
    ShapeTree.Leaf
    Description of a leaf of the Tree, where the geometric information is stored.
    ShapeTree.TreeEntry
    Information of a single object stored in a tree
    ShapeTree.TreeNode
    Common functionality of inner nodes and leaf nodes.
    Signum
    Implements the mathematical signum function.
    TimeLimit
    Class used to cancel a performance critical algorithm after a time limit is exceeded.
    UndoableObjects
    Database of objects, for which Undo and Redo operations are made possible.
    UndoableObjects.UndoableObjectNode
    Stores informations for correct restoring or cancelling an object in an undo or redo operation.
